abstract: Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro said his American counterpart Donald Trump assured him on Friday that he will not impose tariffs on the South American country's steel and aluminum.
snippet: Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro said his American counterpart Donald Trump assured him on Friday that he will not impose tariffs on the South American country's steel and aluminum.
lead_paragraph: RIO DE JANEIRO — Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro said his American counterpart Donald Trump assured him on Friday that he will not impose tariffs on the South American country's steel and aluminum.
headline_main: Bolsonaro Says U.S. Won't Impose Tariffs on Brazilian Steel
headline_print_headline: Bolsonaro Says U.S. Won't Impose Tariffs on Brazilian Steel

abstract: Elizabeth Warren, Pete Buttigieg and Amy Klobuchar are trying to knock each other out in the Iowa caucuses, where they need strong finishes to stay viable in the 2020 race.
snippet: Elizabeth Warren, Pete Buttigieg and Amy Klobuchar are trying to knock each other out in the Iowa caucuses, where they need strong finishes to stay viable in the 2020 race.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — As Elizabeth Warren and Amy Klobuchar escalated their attacks on Pete Buttigieg in Thursday night’s Democratic debate, and Mr. Buttigieg forcefully pushed back, a crucial if unspoken fact was driving the political combat: All three candidates are trying to knock each other out in the Iowa caucuses, where they need strong finishes to stay viable in the 2020 race.

abstract: President Donald Trump escaped the chill of Washington and his impeachment on Friday to celebrate Christmas and New Year's in sunny Florida with family and friends.
snippet: President Donald Trump escaped the chill of Washington and his impeachment on Friday to celebrate Christmas and New Year's in sunny Florida with family and friends.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump escaped the chill of Washington and his impeachment on Friday to celebrate Christmas and New Year's in sunny Florida with family and friends.

abstract: West Point and Naval Academy investigations found that cadets and midshipmen were playing “the circle game” during an ESPN broadcast of the Army-Navy game on Saturday.
snippet: West Point and Naval Academy investigations found that cadets and midshipmen were playing “the circle game” during an ESPN broadcast of the Army-Navy game on Saturday.
lead_paragraph: Military officials said on Friday that their investigations had found that Army cadets and Navy midshipmen who flashed hand symbols during a nationally televised football pregame show last week were playing a juvenile game known as “the circle game,” and not making hand gestures associated with white nationalists and other hate groups.

abstract: Soaring rates of homelessness in California, which is struggling with out-of-reach housing costs and affordable housing construction, pulled that figure upward.
snippet: Soaring rates of homelessness in California, which is struggling with out-of-reach housing costs and affordable housing construction, pulled that figure upward.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Homelessness in the United States continued to rise this year, driven by soaring rates of homelessness in California, according to a new federal report that could prompt long-promised action for people living in the streets of Los Angeles and San Francisco.

abstract: Joe Biden has been fighting a stutter since childhood, and he said Friday he has no regrets about talking openly about it after one of his responses in Thursday's presidential debate prompted a mocking tweet from former White House press secretary Sarah Sanders.
snippet: Joe Biden has been fighting a stutter since childhood, and he said Friday he has no regrets about talking openly about it after one of his responses in Thursday's presidential debate prompted a mocking tweet from former White House press secretary...
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Joe Biden has been fighting a stutter since childhood, and he said Friday he has no regrets about talking openly about it after one of his responses in Thursday's presidential debate prompted a mocking tweet from former White House press secretary Sarah Sanders.
headline_main: Biden: No Regrets for Talking Openly About Stuttering
headline_print_headline: Biden: No Regrets for Talking Openly About Stuttering

abstract: Amid intense focus on impeachment and year-end deals on spending and trade, the Senate hurtled this week toward a less-heralded accomplishment: confirming another batch of conservative judges.

abstract: A judge on Friday revoked the grazing permit of two ranchers who were pardoned last year by President Donald Trump on an arson conviction for setting fire to federal lands.
snippet: A judge on Friday revoked the grazing permit of two ranchers who were pardoned last year by President Donald Trump on an arson conviction for setting fire to federal lands.
lead_paragraph: PORTLAND, Ore. — A judge on Friday revoked the grazing permit of two ranchers who were pardoned last year by President Donald Trump on an arson conviction for setting fire to federal lands.
headline_main: Judge Revokes Grazing Permit for Ranchers Pardoned by Trump
headline_print_headline: Judge Revokes Grazing Permit for Ranchers Pardoned by Trump
